==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Astronomical
<hw>As`tro*nom"ic*al</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>astronomicus</ets>, Gr. <grk>'astronomiko`s</grk>: cf. F.
<ets>astronomique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to astronomy; in
accordance with the methods or principles of astronomy.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>As`tro*nom"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Astronomical clock</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Clock</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Astronomical day</b></col>. <cd>See
under <er>Day</er>.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Astronomical
fractions</b></col>, <col><b>Astronomical numbers</b></col></mcol>.
<cd>See under <er>Sexagesimal</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Astronomize</ent>⟦br⟧
